{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M5z3AKiXAFQpEqr7DFt7bq","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# nginx-ingress/ingress_canary\n2\t#\n3\t# Two backends (stable and canary) exist in the demo namespace. A canary\n4\t# Ingress is present but not routing header-based traffic. The agent must\n5\t# configure the canary Ingress so X-Canary: always routes to the canary\n6\t# backend and all other requests go to stable.\n7\t\n8\tparams:\n9\t  host:\n10\t    default: canary.example.com\n11\t    description: Hostname both the stable and canary Ingress serve.\n12\t  header_name:\n13\t    default: X-Canary\n14\t    description: Request header that selects the canary backend.\n15\t  header_value:\n16\t    default: always\n17\t    description: Header value that routes traffic to the canary backend.\n18\t  stable_body:\n19\t    default: stable\n20\t    description: Response body returned by the stable backend.\n21\t  canary_body:\n22\t    default: canary\n23\t    description: Response body returned by the canary backend.\n24\t  curl_pod_name:\n25\t    default: curl-test\n26\t    description: Name of the in-cluster pod used to issue test requests.\n27\t\n28\tprompt: |\n29\t  Two backend services exist in the demo namespace:\n30\t  - stable: returns \"{{params.stable_body}}\"\n31\t  - canary: returns \"{{params.canary_body}}\"\n32\t\n33\t  A stable Ingress routes {{params.host}} to the stable backend.\n34\t  A canary Ingress exists, but canary traffic is not reaching the canary\n35\t  backend.\n36\t\n37\t  Your task:\n38\t  1) Requests with header \"{{params.header_name}}: {{params.header_value}}\" must route to the canary backend.\n39\t  2) Requests without that header must route to the stable backend.\n40\t\n41\t  Do not modify the application Deployments or Services.\n42\t\n43\t  Use these requests to test:\n44\t  ```bash\n45\t  kubectl -n demo exec {{params.curl_pod_name}} -- curl -sS -H \"Host: {{params.host}}\" \\\n46\t    http://ingress-ng