{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CAwsDuFUJM48ZyYm4cTWqB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No mention of `canary-echo` in the nginx config at all. The canary routing is completely absent.\n\nThe error `unable to find real backend for alternative backend demo-canary-echo-80. Deleting.` is the key. Let me dig deeper into what this error means in nginx-ingress v1.14.1.\n\nLet me look at the controller source code logic. In nginx-ingress, the function that generates this error is in `controller.go`. The error at line 1697 (from the log) suggests the controller is:\n\n1. Processing the canary Ingress\n2. Building the \"alternative backend\" list\n3. Trying to find the \"real backend\" that corresponds to each alternative backend\n4. Failing to find it and deleting the alternative backend\n\nThe \"real backend\" it's looking for is the backend from the PRIMARY Ingress. The primary Ingress `canary-stable` routes `canary.example.com /` to `stable-echo:80`. But I'm wondering if the issue is that the primary Ingress has multiple paths like `/health` and `/` both pointing to `stable-echo:80`, while the canary Ingress only has `/` pointing to `canary-echo:80`. When the controller merges these, it might be creating a single backend that doesn't properly match the canary backend.\n\nIn nginx-ingress, each unique service:port combination gets one backend named `<namespace>-<service>-<port>`, so the primary Ingress creates `demo-stable-echo-80` and the canary creates `demo-canary-echo-80`. The merging algorithm should find the real backend by matching paths—the canary's `/` (Exact) should correspond to the primary's `/` (Exact), both using `demo-stable-echo-80`. But it's not finding that match, which is why it's deleting the canary backend instead.\n\nMaybe the issue is that the primary Ingress isn't being recognized correctly, or the backend structure isn't what I expect. Let me check what backends actually exist in the nginx configuration to see what's really happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":151,"cache_read_input_tokens":66610,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":151},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e2fd028f-f289-4ccb-a409-2b47e5cd3f27","uuid":"e7a5c449-b68b-4f1d-8265-a763f90bcfac","request_id":"req_011Cc6d56r1zWsDYmdHKo7et"}
