{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YXi8AqzCjVRtgRNSyFxtCV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No redirect (no 3xx). Direct 404. This is a genuine 404 from nginx.\n\nNow, nginx has a `location /` block for `canary.example.com`. The request goes to `canary.example.com /`. The location should match. But we get 404.\n\nWait - maybe the issue is the `pathType: Exact`. In nginx-ingress, when `pathType: Exact` is used with path `/`, it generates `location = /` (with the `=` modifier) in nginx config. But the config I see shows `location /` (without `=`).\nActually, I need to look at the full nginx config output more carefully—I only saw the location block snippet. Let me check if there's another location block matching first, or try a different path to see if it's path-specific. I'm also wondering if the SSL redirect handling in nginx-ingress might be interfering here.\n\nLooking at the 404 response itself—it's nginx's default 404 page with 146 bytes, which suggests the request is falling through to the `upstream-default-backend` instead of matching a proper upstream. So the flow is likely: request comes in with `Host: canary.example.com` and path `/`, nginx matches the `location /` block, but then can't find the right upstream and falls back to the default backend which returns 404.\n\nThe issue is probably that the Lua balancer isn't updating `$proxy_upstream_name` to `demo-stable-echo-80` as it should. This could happen if the backend isn't being loaded into the Lua shared dictionary from the `/configuration/backends` API endpoint.\n\nBut there's another layer to this: nginx-ingress uses a mapping between the location variables (`$namespace`, `$ingress_name`, `$service_name`, `$service_port`, `$location_path`) and the actual backend name. This mapping comes from a different configuration source than the backends list itself. I should check the `/configuration/general` and `/configuration/servers` endpoints to see if that mapping is correct, or look at the nginx-ingress debug endpoints to inspect the Lua configuration directly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2294,"cache_read_input_tokens":73538,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2294},"output_tokens":17,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e2fd028f-f289-4ccb-a409-2b47e5cd3f27","uuid":"83bea61c-52a7-4d6a-a362-fe932aff180b","request_id":"req_011Cc6dEPqiJuS8B2czKWE3k"}
